                <h3>Step 1: Decide to Sell</h3>
                <p>Once you have decided to sell your home, you want to get as much profit as possible. One of the most important factors that influences the price is timing. There is no doubt that you will sell your home only if there would be enough buyers and a great demand on it. Unfortunately, the more houses are being sold, the less chances you have to make a great deal. A lot of factors are also connected with season, since the rate of houses selling starts increasing at the end of the winter.</p>
                <p>Moreover, your house can be highly evaluated if it has a pleasant appearance. Despite whatever amount of money you have, there are many ways of house improvement. For example, it can be easily renovated by using a total alteration as well as simple walls repainting.</p>
                <p>In many cases, customers enjoy the pleasant atmosphere around your house. Tidily cutted grass and well-groomed flowerbed attract more people to your house.</p>
                <p>If you are still afraid that your house can be undervalued, you can lead a revision of your house. Such inspection is a chance for you to make a great impression on customers. If everything goes well, there would not be any unpredictable occasions in future.</p>
                <p>Everything's completed? Get ready to sign the most advantageous sale! </p>
                <h3>Step 2: Hire a Professional Agent</h3>
                <p>Thousands of real estate agents propose a lot of services and it makes some difficulties when you are choosing the one, that will suit you best. That's why we've decided to give you several tips on choosing the professional.</p>
                <p>Select accurately. Real estate agent represents your interests and you have to be sure that your representative will do anything possible to prove his/her skills. As a result, mutual confidence and understanding will be the basis of your relations.</p>
                <p>This is how we recommend you to find a professional Realtor:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Note down some names and numbers which can be found in “For Sale” signs;</li>
                    <li>Ask for advice your friends or family;</li>
                    <li>Call or visit personally one of the local offices;</li>
                </ul>
                <p>The professional agent has to know the local area and trends in the real estate market. By the way, you have to expect for quality services and prompt goal achievement from such real estate agent.</p>
                <h3>Step 3: List your house</h3>
                <p>After you have found the professional real estate agent, they will get to work. First of all, the process of listing your home will start with house evaluation and fix the price. Information about your house on market data will be negotiated according to the prices in a local area.</p>
                <p>Now, when everything is ready, the agent will sell your house by using as many ways as possible. They will do everything to make buyers pay attention to your house. Their methods are based on marketing houses through different listing sites and media. For instance, it can be social media, websites, various blogs or Multiple Listing Service (MLS).</p>
                <p>In addition to this, all buyers will have a possibility to review the interior of your house. To have some imagery about living in your house, realtors also offer staging the house to customers.</p>
                <h3>Step 4: Get an Offer</h3>
                <p>You hire a real estate agent to avoid any inequality or troubles during all period of selling your house. They will find you out all information regarding the terms and price, which will be the most suitable for you and the buyer. Financing conditions, any buyer’s inclusions or exclusions will be also the subject of their work.</p>
                <p>
                    The deal provides meeting the expectations of seller and buyer, that is why the person who buys your house may also ask for making some changes in your home, before the deal conclusion. It can be the rearrangement of furniture, some appliances, or even small renovations inside your house. You have to expect that buyer can also add in longer or shorter terms of your deal.
                </p>
                <p>You can suggest your own wishes as well. Negotiate everything with a buyer to reach the mutual agreement and make a beneficial deal for both parties.</p>
                <h3>Step 5: Close the Sale</h3>
                <p>The key stage of selling your house will be the closing costs, which include mortgage fees, some inspections and legal expenses. As soon as everything is done, you are welcome to say goodbye to your old house and pass keys to the new owners. Our congratulations!</p>
                <h3 class="centered">You have made a successful bargain and your house is officially sold!</h3>
